Added overloads to HasMany so the child type can be inferred by the property in most cases. If the property type derives from IEnumerable<CHILD> or IDictionary<KEY, CHILD>, the CHILD will be used as the property type.

Now 90% of the time you can do this:
  HasMany(x => x.Users);

instead of:
  HasMany<User>(x => x.Users);


